Da igitur quaeso negotium Pharnaci, An- taeo, Salvio, ut id nomen ex omnibus libris tollatur.” Pharnaces and the rest were ‘librarii ' of Atticus, who had oihers also whom Cicero mentions. They copied manu- scripts for Atticus, and he made money by the business. We may perhaps owe a good deal to him for multiplying copies and giving Cicero's 1101115, and particularly his letters, a better chance of preservation. <Ne- pOS‚ Life of Atticus, c. 13.)
